Ad Information Plots

Overview of advertising exposure and interaction:

I observed the number of adverts users saw when scrolling over a 5-minute period at different times of the day (morning/afternoon/evening/late night), and recorded whether each advert resulted in an interaction. The number of records for different types of advert interactions is about 12 for low interactions, 11 for high interactions, and 2 for medium interactions. Low Interaction was the most common, indicating that most users did not engage in deep interactions such as clicking; Medium Interaction had the lowest number.

Plot1

The distribution of the number of advertisements at different times

The density plot show that the number of advertisements per 5 mins during four different time of one day. The afternoon (from 12 PM to 6 PM) and evening (from 6 PM to 12 PM) are the periods with the highest advertising exposure rates, which are consistent with the times when user activity is high. The amount of ads in late night decrease showing that the users activities on the internet declining. The advertising exposing maintain moderate in the morning. This indicate that the periods the most suitable for advertising is afternoon and evening time.

Distribution of relevance scores for advertisements in each product category

This box plot distribute the advertising relevance scores in different product categories: beauty, fitness, fashion, food, others, and technology. The relevance scores of technology advertisements shows the most variability and the median is close to 4, indicating that although some users consider these advertisements highly relevant, others lacks interest in them. The relevance score of beauty and fitness advertisements are similar, relatively low, with a median score of approximately 3. The distribution of food advertisements is similar to that of fashion advertisements, with a median relevance score of approximately 4. The fashion and food advertisements are often regarded as more relevant and influential. Due to the not enoght data about other type advertisements, it indicates insufficient response and the inability to provide meaningful conclusions.

## Summary For Plot 1, most users with interaction with advertisements are classified as low interaction group. This indicates that most advertisements fail to effectively attract users, so the content needs improvement to enhance users active engagement. For Plot 2, the advertising exposure volume peaks during the afternoon and evening periods, advertisers can choose to deliver advertisements during these two time periods. For Plot 3, advertisements related to fashion and food have higher relevance levels, indicating that the content in these categories is more targeted. Mangers might need more precise content strategy.

The findings suggest that although fashion and food adverts are effective in attracting user interest, the content strategy for beauty, fitness and technology adverts could be enhanced to increase relevance and interaction levels, particularly during peek exposure times in the afternoon and evening.
